# DNS suffixes the firewall VM's dnsmasq will resolve. Matched as a
# suffix (so `github.com` here lets `api.github.com` resolve too —
# dnsmasq's `server=/HOST/...` syntax matches HOST and all subdomains).
# Anything else returns 0.0.0.0 via the catch-all.

amazonaws.com
github.com
githubusercontent.com
gitlab.com
bitbucket.org
dev.azure.com
visualstudio.com
nixos.org
cachix.org
cloudfront.net
npmjs.org
pypi.org
pythonhosted.org
crates.io
golang.org
